; (not (not X)) is the !! bool-normalization idiom — an INFO nudge (not a warning,
; since it is sometimes intentional). A single (not X) stays silent.
(defn int f ((int x))
  (decl (int b) (not (not x))
        (int c) (not x))
  (return (+ b c)))
;==EXPECTED-WARNING==
<stdin>:4:17: info[macro]: (not (not X)) normalizes to 0/1 (the !! idiom); if you only need truthiness, X alone works
  (decl (int b) (not (not x))
                ^
